Dear TIM students whose TIM projects I will have the pleasure to supervise =
during Winter 2026.
As the year comes to a close, I wanted to take a moment to wish each of you=
 a very happy holiday season and a bright, meaningful future ahead.
I know this time of year can be especially difficult for many of us. Being =
far from home often means missing family, friends, familiar traditions, and=
 the comfort of being with loved ones. Please know that those feelings are =
understood and shared. Even when we are surrounded by opportunity and growt=
h, the distance can still be heavy.
I want you to know this: I will always be here for you =97 in the highs and=
 in the lows. Whether you are celebrating successes or working through chal=
lenges, you do not walk this journey alone. Supporting you, believing in yo=
u, and seeing you grow is a privilege, and you each hold a special place in=
 my heart.
You have shown resilience, courage, and determination by choosing this path=
 far from home. Wherever life takes you next, I have no doubt that you will=
 do meaningful things and make a positive impact.
Please take care of yourselves, stay connected to those you love, and know =
that you are thought of warmly during this season.
Happy holidays, and my very best wishes to each of you.
Warm regards,
Tony B.


--_000_YQBPR0101MB4459AB93151BD154798BBB559BB2AYQBPR0101MB4459_
